About this item

  • WHY IPAD Colourfully reimagined and more versatile than ever, iPad is great for the things you do every day. With an all-screen design, 27.69 cm (10.9) Liquid Retina display, powerful A14 Bionic chip, superfast Wi-Fi and four gorgeous colours, iPad delivers a powerful way to create, stay connected and get things done.
  • iPadOS + APPS iPadOS makes iPad more productive, intuitive and versatile. With iPadOS, run multiple apps at once, use Apple Pencil to write in any text field with Scribble, and edit and share photos. iPad comes with essential apps like Safari, Messages and Keynote, with over a million more apps available on the App Store.
  • FAST WI-FI CONNECTIVITY Wi-Fi 6 gives you fast access to your files, uploads and downloads, and lets you seamlessly stream your favourite shows.
  • PERFORMANCE AND STORAGE The A14 Bionic chip delivers power and performance for any activity. And with all-day battery life, iPad is perfect for playing immersive games and editing photos and videos. Choose from 64GB or 256GB storage options.
  • APPLE PENCIL AND MAGIC KEYBOARD FOLIO With Apple Pencil (1st generation), iPad transforms into an immersive drawing canvas and the worlds best notetaking device. The Magic Keyboard Folio features a versatile two-piece design with a detachable keyboard and a protective back panel that both attach magnetically to iPad. (Accessories are sold separately.)

    How are ratings calculated?
    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    AVANISH KUMAR THAKUR
    5.0 out of 5 stars Review
    Reviewed in India on 15 June 2024
    Style Name: Wi-FiSize: 64 GBColour: BlueVerified Purchase
    I've been using the iPad 10th Generation for a few months now, and overall, I'm quite impressed with its performance and features. Here's my take on it:

    Pros:

    1.Performance: The A13 Bionic chip makes a noticeable difference in speed and responsiveness. Apps launch quickly, and multitasking feels smooth even with several apps open.

    2. Display: The Retina display is vibrant and sharp, perfect for watching videos, browsing the web, and reading. It's also bright enough to use comfortably in various lighting conditions.

    3. Battery Life: I can easily get through a full day of moderate use on a single charge. Apple's claim of up to 10 hours seems accurate based on my experience.

    4. Build Quality:The aluminum build feels premium and sturdy. It's lightweight enough to hold comfortably but doesn't feel cheap or flimsy.

    5. iPadOS:The software experience is excellent. iPadOS offers useful features like Split View and Slide Over, which enhance productivity. It's also intuitive if you're already familiar with iOS.

    Cons:

    1. Camera:The cameras are decent for video calls and casual photography, but they're not exceptional. Don't expect the same quality as the latest iPhones.

    2. Storage Options: The base model starts at 64GB, which can fill up quickly if you use a lot of apps or store media. Consider opting for higher storage configurations if you need more space.

    The iPad 10th Generation is a fantastic tablet, especially for the price. It strikes a good balance between performance, design, and functionality. Whether you're using it for work, entertainment, or education, it handles everything well. It integrates seamlessly with other Apple devices, which is a big plus if you're already in the Apple ecosystem. I would recommend it to anyone looking for a reliable and versatile tablet that doesn't break the bank.
